On Thu, Mar 23, 2000 at 09:41:05PM -0500, Gregory Maxwell wrote:
> I think people would be best served by a routing howto and an advanced
> routing howto, so people who want the basic stuff won't have to deal with
> diffserve, OSPF, and token bucket filters.
Or one big HOWTO with a lot of sections. It doesn't really matter if it's
one or two documents. Advanced users just skip the earlier chapters.
I think we can safely leave OSPF & BGP out - I think Zebra comes with some
documentation, and there are excellent books describing these protocols,
which aren't Unix specific.
